        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Calculated based on literature value and estimate. 

10E+5 ton/year of zinc oxide is produced globally (Klingshirn, 2007). Three basic technologies of zinc production exists. It is assumed, that the total production volume is distributed between these three technologies evenly.

The global value is scaled to the European production volume using GDP, PPP (International Monetary Fund), for year 2005; 1.44E+13 current international dollar as GDP_PPP for Europe and 5.65E+13 current international dollar as GDP_PPP for the whole world.</productionVolumeComment>
