        <comment xml:lang="en">Estimated value based on expert judgement. The amount of heat required for this process can vary greatly depending on the furnace design. The fuel consumption ranges from 120 L to over 250 L of heavy oil per tonne of zinc oxide (Jiyang 2009). Based on this range, an amount of 8 MJ of heat per kg of zinc oxide is assumed to be consumed. 

